## Two different “done” signals

| Signal | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| **`lib/self-host-sv0-loop.list` green** | Each listed **`.sv0`** seed: SML emits C twice deterministically, **`cc`**+**`run`** exits **0**, and (unless skipped) **`sv0-self-host-emit-c.sh`** stdout **`diff`**s SML — **harness health**, not full compiler self-host. |
| **`bootstrap-sml-final` + `sml-legacy/`** | **Stakeholder bar** from **`task/sv0-toolchain-milestone-3-self-host.Rmd`**: feature parity, VM policy, **then** tag on **sv0c only**, move **`sml/`** → **`sml-legacy/`**, default build **sv0-only**. |

Growing the pilot list **is** real progress toward M3 (more transliterated surface is exercised end-to-end on the C path). It **does not** satisfy SML retirement by itself.

## Agent discipline

- Never tag **`bootstrap-sml-final`** or rename **`sml/`** because the self-host **pilot** list grew — retirement follows the **completion criteria** in the M3 task.
- When adding paths to **`self-host-sv0-loop.list`**, verify **`./scripts/sv0 emit-c <rel>`** + **`cc`** + **`./a.out`** (exit **0**) locally first; keep CI time in mind.
- Prefer **`SV0_SELF_HOST_COMPILER`** documentation and **`doc/self-host-sv0-loop.md`** updates when changing loop semantics or pilot counts.
- Normative language semantics still come from **`sv0doc/`**; self-host work does not redefine the language.

